14. What is the purpose of the try clause? What is the purpose of the except clause?
--->TRY CLAUSE: try clause is used when you think that program can crash so you try
    to run the program and it crashes it wont disturb other part of program

    EXCEPT CLAUSE: except clause is used when you are trying a certain part 
    of program but it fails so it used as a response to exception.
